					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's perfectly plausible that &quot;more blues&quot; meant &quot;in comparison to most 2nd generation video game consoles&quot;. The Intellivision, Channel F, OdysseyÂ², as well as the contemporary computers (e.g. VIC-20, Atari 400, Apple 2) had very limited master palettes.<br /><br />Thus, it could have been part of the original design document that specifically led to the cost-reduction choice of using a single (NTSCÃ—6) master clock instead of needing the TMS9928's need for both a (NTSCÃ—3/2) and (NTSCÃ—2) clock.<br /><br />(They didn't <em>have</em> to pick that pixel clock. They didn't <em>have</em> to provide colors from all 12 equally-spaced angles around the YUV plane)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

