						<div class="postbody">It is (and it's an interesting perspective), but then again, Betoux identifies one red. I'm on the verge saying the nes master palette has no red colour, or 1 i'd call red in a pinch, while there's several i'd call green, blue, purple. I realize this is a personal judgement, but still...<br /><br />It's like bregalad says, but at the same time our names for colours are varyingly narrow/broad in definition, and i'm inclined to say that it's mostly cultural rather than individual, at least at a pattern level. Human biology may play a part, too.</div>

					
